ump took ownership of ending talks with Democrats on further relief for millions suffering the economic toll of the pandemic, which has required mass shutdowns of parts of the economy.\n\n\xe2\x80\xa6request, and looking to the future of our Country. I have instructed my representatives to\xc2\xa0stop negotiating until after the election when, immediately after\xc2\xa0I win,\xc2\xa0we will pass a\xc2\xa0major\xc2\xa0Stimulus Bill that focuses on hardworking Americans and Small Business. I have asked\xe2\x80\xa6\n\xe2\x80\x94 Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) October 6, 2020\n\nRepublican allies are peeling away from Trump, with some calling his decision to withdraw from virus aid talks a mistake.\nSome, including Trump, have suggested that individual bills allowing for another round of $1,200 stimulus cheques be signed. Democrats have signalled unwillingness to handle further aid with a piecemeal approach.\nMcConnell held out hope that \xe2\x80\x9cwe ought to continue to talk\xe2\x80\x9d even as several of his own senators said they do not want to pass more aid.\nPresident Donald Trump removes his mask as he stands on the Blue Room Balcony upon returning to the White House after leaving Walter Reed National Military Medical Center, where he was treated for COVID-19 [Alex Brandon/AP Photo]\xe2\x80\x9cThere\xe2\x80\x99s no question that the proximity to the election has made this much more challenging,\xe2\x80\x9d McConnell said, referencing upcoming national elections for Congress and the presidency.\nIn his November 3 election bid to retain his Senate seat, McConnell faces a long-shot challenge from Democrat Amy McGrath, a former Marine Corps fighter pilot.\nFirst lady Melania Trump and several White House officials including spokeswoman Kayleigh McEnany have also tested positive for the deadly disease.\nTrump\xe2\x80\x99s handling of his infection and the broader coronavirus pandemic \xe2\x80\x93 which has killed more than 211,000 Americans, more than in any other country \xe2\x80\x93 is threatening Republicans\xe2\x80\x99 hopes of keeping their Senate majority.\nIn the Senate, lawmakers are encouraged to wear masks, practice social distancing and limit office visitors. Committee hearings are conducted partly online, and there have been calls for new testing protocols.\n\xe2\x80\x9cSince May 1st, I\xe2\x80\x99ve said wear your mask and practice social distancing. It\xe2\x80\x99s the only way that we know of to prevent the spread until we get a vaccine and we\xe2\x80\x99ve practiced that in the Senate,\xe2\x80\x9d\xc2\xa0McConnell\xc2\xa0said.\n\nSenate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell said he has avoided visiting the White House for more than two months because of its handling of the coronavirus https://t.co/EoS1szcKCt pic.twitter.com/2KaUjakuqf\n\xe2\x80\x94 Reuters (@Reuters) October 8, 2020\n\n\xe2\x80\x9cYou\xe2\x80\x99ve heard about other places that have had a different view, and they are paying a price for it,\xe2\x80\x9d he said.\nThree Republican senators have tested positive for COVID-19. Two were diagnosed after attending a crowded White House event for Trump\xe2\x80\x99s Supreme Court nominee Amy Coney Barrett.\nSource : News AgenciesMore from News\xe2\x80\x98We need to live\xe2\x80\x99: Young Nigerians on why they are protestingPremier League clubs reject \xe2\x80\x98Project Big Picture\xe2\x80\x99Will Zambia be first African nation to default during pandemic?Timeline: A year of bloody protests in GuineaMost ReadTurkey denies sending Syrian fighters: Nagorno-Karabakh live newsLadakh Buddhists who hailed India\xe2\x80\x99s Kashmir move not so sure nowSaudi Arabia fails in bid for seat on UN Human Rights CouncilWhat\xe2\x80\x99s in a photo? A lot for Lebanon as talks with Israel beginAbout\xd8\xaa\xd8\xa8\xd8\xaf\xd9\x8a\xd9\x84 \xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd9\x82\xd8\xa7\xd8\xa6\xd9\x85\xd8\xa9About UsCode of EthicsTerms and ConditionsPrivacy PolicyCookie PolicyCookie PreferencesCommunity GuidelinesWork for usHR QualityConne